ursday%20showed%20frame-by-frame%20images%20of%20the%20General%20Electric-made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fups-cargo-plane-crash-kentucky-left-engine-detached-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eengine%20completely%20coming%20off%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20then%20smashing%20into%20the%20body%20of%20the%20Honolulu-bound%20plane%20as%20the%20aircraft%20took%20off.%20It%20also%20included%20photos%20of%20the%20wreckage%20being%20studied%20in%20the%20NTSB%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20%26quot%3Bfound%20evidence%20of%20fatigue%20cracks%20in%20addition%20to%20areas%20of%20overstress%20failure%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20part%20that%20attached%20the%20McDonnell%20Douglas%20MD-11%20freighter's%20left%20engine%20to%20the%20wing%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20crew%20members%20on%20the%20plane%20and%2011%20people%20on%20the%20ground%20were%20killed%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Another%2023%20people%20on%20the%20ground%20were%20injured.%20The%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fups-plane-crash-louisville-airport-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20plane%20crash%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20a%20trail%20of%20destruction%20in%20an%20industrial%20area%20near%20Louisville's%20Muhammad%20Ali%20International%20Airport%2C%20satellite%20images%20in%20the%20report%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20the%20plane%20initially%20climbed%20to%20about%2030%20feet%20above%20ground%20and%20cleared%20a%20fence%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20runway%20before%20its%20main%20landing%20gear%20hit%20the%20roof%20of%20a%20UPS%20warehouse%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20airport.%20The%20plane%20then%20hit%20a%20storage%20yard%20and%20two%20other%20buildings%2C%20including%20a%20petroleum%20recycling%20facility%2C%20and%20was%20mostly%20consumed%20by%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aeb7b7a5-4d3c-4b58-9f39-862f22dd7ac9%5C%22%3EMetal%20fatigue%20crashes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MD-11%20involved%20was%20a%2034-year-old%20tri-engine%20widebody%20jet%20that%20was%20first%20delivered%20to%20Thai%20Airways%20in%201991%2C%20before%20being%20acquired%20by%20UPS%20in%202006.%20Boeing%20merged%20with%20McDonnell%20Douglas%20in%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20grounded%20the%20MD11%20fleet%2C%20which%20UPS%20and%20FedEx%20use%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlane%20crashes%20caused%20by%20metal%20fatigue%20are%20rare%2C%20but%20similar%20accidents%20have%20occurred%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThursday's%20report%20referenced%20a%20similar%20but%20much%20deadlier%20crash%20in%201979.%20American%20Airlines%20flight%20191%2C%20a%20McDonnell-Douglas%20DC-10-10%20aircraft%2C%20crashed%20into%20an%20open%20field%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20runway%20at%20Chicago-O'Hare%20International%20Airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20takeoff%2C%20the%20left%20engine%20on%20the%20left%20wing%20separated%20from%20the%20airplane%20and%20fell%20onto%20the%20runway.%20The%20airplane%20was%20destroyed%20in%20the%20crash%20and%20subsequent%20fire%2C%20and%20273%20people%2C%20including%20two%20people%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20were%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20in%202018%2C%20Southwest%20Airlines%20Flight%201380%20experienced%20an%20uncontained%20engine%20failure%20in%20the%20left%20engine%20after%20departing%20from%20New%20York's%20LaGuardia%20Airport%20en%20route%20to%20Dallas.%20The%20incident%20killed%20a%20window%20seat%20passenger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20a%20Southwest%20flight%20blew%20an%20engine%20as%20it%20flew%20from%20New%20Orleans%20to%20Orlando%2C%20and%20shrapnel%20tore%20a%20five-by-16-inch%20hole%20just%20above%20the%20wing.%20The%20plane%20landed%20safely.%20The%20NTSB%20said%20a%20fan%20blade%20had%20broken%20off%20because%20of%20metal%20fatigue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Thursday's%20report%2C%20the%20NTSB%20said%20its%20investigation%20of%20UPS%20flight%202976%20is%20ongoi